The White House Office of National Drug Control Policy (ONDCP) has released a report on the President's Commission on Combating Drug Addiction and the Opioid Crisis. The report highlights the progress made by the Trump Administration in addressing addiction and the opioid crisis through prevention, interdiction, and treatment. The efforts have resulted in a 5% decrease in reported provisional overdose deaths for the 12-month period ending in September 2018. The full report can be accessed through the provided link.